inn1.comm: full inswinger to start the proceedings, McCullum gets forward rather hesitantly and pushes it off the inner half of the bat to the on side
around the off stump, full, no movement this time, defended to the off side

Umpire Dharmasena has sent Ryder on his way. Lbw. It landed full on the off and middle line and moved in to hit Ryder in front of the middle. Ryder was looking to play across the line and is a dead duck. It would have crashed into the leg stump.
full in length, on the off stump line, Guptill pushes it out to the off side
around that off stump again, Guptill leans forward to push it towards mid-off
just outside off, moving away, defended to point
Two-left arm seamers sharing the new ball. RP gets the ball full and on the middle and off line, pushed back down the track
lands outside leg, moves in a touch, McCullum tries to clip it through the on side ,misses and is struck on the pad
length delivery on the middle and off line, McCullum stays back to punch it down to mid-on. NZ won the toss and chose to bat on a dry slow wicket
fuller, straightening on the middle, trying to get the lbw decision, McCullum takes out the front leg from the way, brings his bat in front in a hurry to keep it out
length delivery moving towards off stump, pushed towards mid-on
good delivery; the best of the lot so far. It nipped back in sharply, took McCullum by surprise and hit the pad but it was going down leg side. Stifled appeal from the Indians.
bangs it in short as he sees McCullum charging out and it's swatted past square-leg for couple of runs

That's the 100th ODI wicket for Nehra. It landed on a length on the leg and middle and hit him in right in front of the middle. Plumb. And it appears as if it did hit the pad first too. What a comeback this is proving  for Nehra after years in wilderness.
around 133 kmph, lands outside off and moves away, left alone
short in length, on the hips, tucked behind square-leg for a single
leans forward to defend the length delivery to the off side.
beaten outside off stump. It was a delivery angling away from him and he flirts with it.

almost caught at square-leg. It held its line on the leg and middle line, Taylor was getting too much across, fell over a touch, got his bat around the front pad and some how manages to wrist it past the lunging Yusuf Pathan
fuller, looking for that lbw again, Taylor drives to mid-on
swings in a touch, moves in to hit the pad but clearly going down the leg side
in the channel outside off stump, goes past the outside edge and Dhoni, the wicketkeeper, collects
another one in the zone, Taylor looks initially to play at it before withdrawing his bat inside the line.

edged but it falls short of Sachin at first slip. Another full delivery angling away, Taylor pushes at it and nicks it to the left of the diving SRT who couldn't stop it from running away to the boundary
goes right back to defend to the off side
fuller, outside off stump, left alone. NZ are wobbling here at 13 for 2.
this one straightens on the off and middle line - another nagging fine delivery from Nehra - and it runs off the inner edge past square-leg. Nehra has been getting the ball to skid
length delivery on the middle, Taylor stabs it to his pad. He has been trying for that lbw, now I reckon one would go across Taylor
This one does move away a fraction and Taylor leans across to push it to the covers
high bouncer on the leg stump line, Taylor ducks under it
on the leg and middle line, Guptill holds his balance and clips the ball through midwicket for three runs
gets forward to push a length delivery to mid-off
There is the Taylor swat that we have come to expect from him. He picked the full length delivery from outside off and went for the big across-the-line swing and edges it past square-leg
short in length, moving outside off stump, guided to backward point where DKarthik makes the stop

NZ continue to wobble here. Taylor has been nicked out. It landed short of length and left Taylor who pushed at it; he did try to withdraw his bat at the last minute but it was too late by then. Edge and gone. Dhoni lunged to his right to collect that.
lands on a length around off stump and moves away, left alone
Wallop! Lovely pull from the happy hooker. Guptill rocked back to pull  the short delivery through wide midwicket region
pushed right of point and runs with the shot. DKarthik swoops on the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end
beaten outside off. It landed on a length, on the middle and off line and moved away past the defensive prod
stays back to push the ball to the off side
outside off stump, a touch short in length, steered wide of Ishant at third-man region for couple of runs
132.6 kmph, length delivery on the middle and leg, nudged to the on side
lands on the leg and middle line, moves in, Guptill is squared-up by that and squeezes the ball off the outer edge to backward point
full and outside off, left alone
leans across to defend the length delivery to the off side. Sachin in the first slip and Dravid at a wide almost fourth slip position
hangs back to punch the back-of-length delivery to mid-off
short of length, around off stump, pushed out to covers. He was bowling a touch fuller length but in the last over or so has retreated to back of a length.
pushes it fuller, outside off, in the channel outside off, left alone
short in length, on the off stump line, tapped close on the off side and before Raina can swoop in from covers, they complete the single
short in length, moving towards the off stump, defended to the off side
fuller, lands on the middle and leg, moves towards middle, pushed back to Nehra
beaten outside off stump. It curved away with the left-armer's angle, and the batsman hung his bat away from the body but luckily, for him, the ball rushed past the outside edge
fuller, he didn't quite get on to the front foot but just lunged across at the last minute to drive it through covers
on the middle and leg, stays back to work it through wide midwicket
Two slips watch as IShant bowls a full delivery on the off stump line, defended towards the off side.
full in length again , pushed to mid-on. He usually hits the short of length but has suffered in the limited overs cricket in the recent months. He has started by hitting the full length here.
back of length, just outside off, holds its  line, left alone
130.8 kmph, full length delivery outside off stump, straightens outside off, left alone
leans forward, gets behind the line to defend the length delivery to off side.
full in length, just outside off stump, stays in that region, left alone and Dhoni collects
short in length, moves across from the middle and leg line, tapped back down the track
full in length, just outside off, jabbed to the off side
stays back to steer the slightly slower one to backward point
shuffles across to clip the length delivery on the middle and leg line to deep midwicket region
Just one slip now. Guptill goes right back, takes care not to get squared-up as he defends to the off side of the pitch
fuller, on the middle stump line, defended to the off side
fullish, just outside off, driven to mid-off
full in length, moves in towards off and middle, driven to mid-on
on the middle stump line, whipped through midwicket. RP gives the chase but can't prevent them from taking three runs.
just outside off stump, holds its line, squeezed down to third-man region
banged in short, on the middle stump line, Grant Elliott is surprised and fends it in the air but well short of the short midwicket.
fuller, just outside off, pushed towards extra-cover for a quick single
stands tall to punch a back-of-length delivery to Raina at cover
full pitched on the middle stump line, driven to Harbhajan at mid-on
a touch slower, full around the off stump, defended to the covers
short in length, on the middle and leg line, jabbed close to the on side for a run
fullish, on the middle and off, driven to Harbhajan at mid-on. Harbhajan spits and polishes the ball.
around 129 kmph delivery, on the middle and leg line, stops on the batsman, deflected wide of midwicket fielder for a single
overpitched on the middle, Guptill leans forward to ease it past the diving mid-on fielder.
hits the length this time, just outside off stump, steered to backward point
short in length, around the off stump, defended to the off side
Edged but well clear of the lone slip fielder in Tendulkar. It straightened outside off stump, off the good length, stabbed off the outer edge and it runs down to the boundary.
even fuller, around the off and middle line - clearly Ishant has changed his natural length for this pitch - driven to cover
short in length, homing in on the off stump, defended compactly out to the off side
tossed up full outside off stump, driven to left of Nehra at long-off
pretty full, higher trajectory, drops in at a yorker length outside off, dug out
rotates the strike with a cut to deep-point region
floated outside off stump, guided to backward point
slower through the air, on a length outside off, tapped to backward point again

Yuvraj strikes in his first over. Fine catch by Rahul at first slip. It was pushed through around off stump, turned a touch and Guptill stabbed it low to left of Rahul who makes a sharp catch look very easy
length delivery outside off, edges the defensive prod to left of second slip where Virat Kohli, subbing for Sachin, fields
leans forward to defend the length delivery outside off stump
slower one, around 109 kmph, full and on the middle, defended to the on side
short in length, moving in a touch, tapped close on the off side
banged in short, it climbs ever so slowly on this sluggish track, swatted to deep backward square-leg
lifting delivery angling away from Oram who sways away from the line
just outside off, slow through the air, left alone
stays back to clip it to square-leg
gets forward to push a flighted delivery back to Yuvraj
tossed up, full, flicked to deep backward square-leg region
just outside off, loopy delivery from a slightly round-arm action, squeezed to backward point
gets forward to drive to long-off
picks the flighted delivery from outside off and paddles it to fine-leg region
And so, Harbhajan lands it further outside off and gets good turn, left alone
leans across outside off and guides the ball to cover point
from round the stumps to the lefty, drifts across ,lands on the middle and leg, turns to get the leading edge to the off side
on the middle and leg, this time Oram is more cautious and defends to the on side with the full face of the bat
leans forward to offer the dead-bat
flighted across, full, just outside off, driven to Nehra at long-off
a touch short and its cut to left of sweeper cover
floated on the middle and leg, shoveled in the air to the on side
reaches forward to the pitch of the ball and eases it down to long-on

Dhoni is confident that he has stumped the batsman. It was a nice delivery that drifted in before turning past the lunging batsman. The back foot did drag out and it appears to be on the line or is it just in when Dhoni breaks the stumps. It has been referred upstairs. The line belongs to the umpire and Gamini de Silva rules it  not out. hmmm.. very close call. The benefit of the doubt and all that jazz.
turns sharply from the leg stump, Oram is squared-up and edges it to the off side
turned past square-leg for a single
fetches it from outside off and sweeps it to long leg
drops it a touch short, Oram goes back to push it to the bowler
flighted full just outside leg, flicked to backward square-leg
slip and leg slip in place and Elliott goes right back to defend it back down the track
leans forward to push it to cover
tossed up, Oram takes a couple of steps forward to take it on the full and drives it down to long-on

quicker one, sliding down the leg side, Elliott misses the flick and Dhoni 'catches' it. Loud appeal and it has been given out. The first replay suggests it was off the pad. Will confirm again after more replays.
leans forward to defend to the off side
ooh .. some turn there . It lands on the off stump before spinning away past the prod
goes right back to clip it from the middle-stump line to long leg
turns in from outside off, nudged past square-leg for a single
pushes it through a tad quicker, full and down the leg side, glanced away to the fine-leg boundary
toppie from round the stumps,  Oram edges it to the pad while trying to defend on the front foot
this one spins away slowly, pushed to cover
over-spin on that , around the off stump line, pushed to the off side
skids on towards the middle, ever so slowly, clipped to deep midwicket region
flighted full, driven to Nehra at long-on
full, perhaps too full, nudged past silly point.
stays back to punch a length delivery to Nehra
full, on the off stump line, eased down to long-on where Nehra makes the stop again
turn and bounce there. It jumped away from the off stump, past the prod, and Dhoni collects. Dravid applauds Yuvraj from his position at first slip
a touch short and Broom fists it to deep point
slip and backward short-leg in place and it has been punched down to long-on for a single
lovely off break, lures Oram forward before spinning away from the outer edge
this one goes on straight, still from round the stumps to the left-handed ORam, pushed away to point
tries to sweep from outside off, misses and is hit outside the off stump
gets forward to drive to long-off for a single
flighted full outside off, whipped down to long-on
comes in with the arm, Broom goes right back to force it away wide of deep midwicket
tossed up full, pushed to cover
a tad quicker, worked right of mid-on for a single
leans forward to deflect it to midwicket
takes couple of steps down the track and defends it back down the pitch
floated on the off stump line, worked past square-leg
goes for the sweep, doesn't quite connect well and the ball rolls away to the on side
a touch short, Oram gets on to the back foot to punch it to long-off
stays round the stumps to the right-handed Broom, delivers a floater outside off stump, Broom is caught at the crease and stabs it past Dravid at slip
flighted around off, driven down to long-off
from round the stumps, on the middle stump line, turning into middle and leg, clipped past square-leg
comes down the track and drives to right of RP at long-off
short in length, angling away, mistimes the cut to cover
lands outside leg, rolls off the pad to fine-leg region. Dhoni rushes after the ball.
on the off stump line, dabbed to the off side
short in length, moving towards middle stump, defended back down the pitch
stays back to defend the back-of-length delivery back to Ishant
short in length, around the off stump, bunted to cover
turns in from outside off, slightly short, worked to deep midwicket off the back foot
lands outside off, spins away to evade the attempted sweep
gets forward to defend to the off side
skips down the track, reaches out to chip it over mid-on ... clears the fielder comfortably
gets forward to push it through covers for a single
stretches across to guide the flighted delivery through point and NZ cross 100
Done in by the slower one. It was around 114 kmph, on a length, Oram checked his shot and ended up chipping it straight back to Ishant
pushes it well outside off stump, left alone
closer to the off stump, still angling away, Dan lets it go through to Dhoni
length delivery in the channel outside off stump, left alone
bouncer from round the stumps, Dan hops back to push it down to the on side
just outside off stump, steered to backward point
from round the stumps, on the pads, tucked behind square-leg for a single
tossed up outside off, spins in, Broom goes right back to defend
turns in with some bounce, moves past the waft and bounds off the thigh pad towards short leg
stays back to work it with the turn past square-leg
gets it from outside off and wrists it past square-leg for a single

stays back to punch the off break to between long-on and deep midwicket. They turn back for the second. Harbhajan isn't too happy and says to his fielders  "Ek doosre ka mooh kya dekh rahe ho?!" (why are guys looking at each other's faces?)
back of a length, around the off line, pushed to long-off
looks to turn an in-coming delivery past square leg, but finds the fielder
that's overpitched, and he uses his wrists to fetch it from outside off to beat mid-on - almost a whip - he uses his wrists to good effect
short and wide, and cut away, Raina dives to field at cover but can't prevent one
length ball, shapes up for an off drive but checks the shot at the last moment
back of a length, outside off, and pushed to cover
too full, and wristed down to long-on
delays the delivery, bowls it full and gets an inside edge from Broom - all safe, though
laps this one from in front of off, to fine leg
flighted on the middle stump, gets down to the pitch of it and flicks it away to midwicket
stays back to a fullish delivery and pushes it through the off side

slower delivery off the over, and he gets sharp break from it, draws Vettori forward, pitches middle, beats his defence and allows Dhoni to whip the bails off - third umpire confirms that although Vettori overbalanced, he is safe

and he has struck first up - this is a short innocuous delivery, asking to be hit, which Broom does, but straight and low to Raina at midwicket, who makes no mistake. Dismissals, they don't come softer
flighted around the off-stump line, Mills gets forward in defending
another flighted delivery outside off, opens the face and gets one to the left of point
quicker one, skids on outside off, Dan is beaten on the cut
gets forward to defend to the off side where Raina stops
this time makes contact with the late-cut and gets it past slip
floated outside leg, tapped towards square-leg and Dhoni runs after it
just outside off stump, guided to backward point
goes right back to push it to point region for a easy single
on the pads, turned to deep backward square-leg
quicker, flatter, pings point for yet another single
tossed up full, again on the legs, tickled around the corner for a run
full, driven down to long-on
turns sharply from the off stump, beaten on the forward defensive stroke
stays back to punch it to cover
on the middle stump line, nudged to square-leg
hangs on the back foot , another easy single to long-on. Just four men in the circle
a touch shorter, around off stump, pushed to right of point for a single
short in length, on the middle and leg, turned straight to midwicket
a touch short in length outside off, dabbed away to backward point
on the leg and middle, nurdled to Nehra at fine-leg
short in length, bounces outside off, cut down right of backward point where D Karthik makes a diving half-stop
short in length, around off stump, pushed to the off side
back of length, guided to backward point. No run.
floated full from round the stumps, driven to long-off
slip in for Mills who leans forward to push it back to the bowler
a touch quicker, turned to midwicket
quickish on the off stump line, tapped to the on side of the pitch
on the pads, rolls away to the leg side
drifts in towards middle and leg, raps him on the pad.. stifled appeal from the Indians
homing in on the off stump, full in length, pushed to Tendulkar at mid-on
fires in a bouncer around off stump, Vettori tries to pull but doesn't connect
a touch slower, full, mistimes the drive to right of RP who makes a half-stop.
short in length, on the off and middle, chopped down to backward point
down the leg side, gets past the attempted glance
back of length around off stump, punched to deepish mid-off

No 8. It was a short-of-length delivery moving away from Mills who tried to punch it through the off side but ended up dragging it back to his stumps. It can happen on a slow track such as this. Gary Kirsten applauds from the dressing room.
leans forward to drive through the on side
drifts in to strike the pad on the leg stump line, going down ...
on the off stump, tries to punch it to the off side, edges it to the midwicket
flighted across, slower in the air, edges the drive to the on side
quickish, dabs to the on side
from slightly round-arm action, flighted on the off stump, squeezed off the outer edge to left of backward point
flighted outside off stump, turned to short midwicket
spins in from outside off, bounces as well, beats the defensive prod to hit the pad high
goes back to push the off break back to the bowler
a tad quicker, outside off stump, holds its line, short in length, punched to deep-point region for three runs
turns towards off stump, nudged away to the off side
spins from outside leg, a touch short in length, punched to long-on for a single
on the off stump line, cramps Dan for room but he manages to chop it to right of backward point
high bouncer and Butler sways away from the line.
Butler is standing outside the crease and so, Ishant fires in another short-pitched delivery, swayed away
full in length, outside off stump, left alone
full in length, driven to mid-on
slower one outside off stump, pushed to cover
full in length, on the off stump line, eased down to long-on
lifting delivery angling away from Butler who allows it to pass through to Dhoni
ooh .. another short delivery, well-directed bouncer, face-high, and Butler manages to yank his head away from the line
full delivery, goes for the drive, edges but it falls short of a diving Dhoni
full and outside off stump, checks his drive and the ball goes to cover
chest-high short delivery. Butler does well again to leave it; he drops his wrists, gets his bat out of the way as he sways away
full in length and outside off stump, Dan goes for the drive and is beaten
the bouncer on the middle stump line and Dan ducks. Dharmasena signals that's the one bouncer for the over

Clatter! It landed back of a length around off and middle line and shaped in a touch, Vettori went for an on-the-up drive but pushed his bat outside the line and was beaten as the delivery moved in a touch.
full in length, outside off, Bond shapes to leave it but is late and the ball runs away off the bat-face to third man
rushes through the off stump channel, from back of length, tries to guide it to third man but misses it completely
short in length, cuts back in, runs off the inner edge to left of Dhoni
length delivery on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
just outside off stump, moves away and Dhoni collects
beaten outside off again. Another one that goes away with the angle and Nehra holds his head
another short delivery, tries to swat it across the on side, misses and is struck on the pad
just around the off stump, turned back to the bowler
Wallop! It was full and outside off and it has been thrashed over cover
slower one, fullish, tapped to the off side
banged in short outside off, pushed away on the hop past backward point. 150 up. It's been one turgid phase of play on a slow track. very unattractive cricket.
a slower one, fullish, on the off, steered to point
charges down the track and has a big swing but fails to connect
on a length, on the off stump, pushed towards extra cover
short in length, just outside off, chopped off the inner edge to the keeper
picks it from the off stump and turns it to square-leg
just outside off stump, dabbed to DK at backward point
rushes down the track,. RP hurls it shorter, a big swing and a miss results
full pitched, on the leg stump line, hits the pad .. lbw appeal but it perhaps pitched just outside leg
full again, driven hard straight to Bond who couldn't jump out of the way and it ricochets off his left boot for a single
slower one, Bond shuffles to wrist it from around the off stump past midwicket
lands outside leg stump, moves in a touch ,tapped to the on side
big swing and a miss. It was the slower one, Butler was early into the big shot across the line.
India need 156 to win. It was the bouncer, Butler tries to upper cut it to third man but succeeds in lobbing a dolly to cover!

inn2.comm: length delivery outside off stump, shapes away, left alone.
around the off stump, Karthik leans across to defend it to the off side. TEndulkar does some gardening down the track
short in length, bouncing outside off, guided to point
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
lands on a length outside off and stays in that region, Karthik stretches across, covers his off stump and shoulders arms
curving away from the off stump, run down to third man
bangs it short of length, Karthik reaches out to punch it through point region where Guptill dives but gets an awkward bounce and he is unable to stop it cleanly
just outside off stump, steered to third man for a single
short and wide, Tendulkar reaches out to cut it through covers. He makes contact with the bottom half of his bat
gets across, gets close to the line of the short-of-length delivery outside off and guides it to point
lifting delivery around the off stump, Tendulkar hops to defend it down to the on side
a touch slower, short in length again, guided down to backward point
length delivery curving away from the off stump, left alone
back of length delivery just outside off stump, holds its line, Karthik leans across and has a waft at it.
Got him! It landed on a length just outside off and moved in to hit him on the middle and leg line. It would have missed the leg stump but that's that. New Zealand taste some early success.
just short of length, outside off, Dravid, on his comeback, moves back to punch it to short cover
holds its line outside off, Dravid square drives it to point
fuller, just outside off stump, rushes on straight, Dravid pushes at it, bat away from the body, and is beaten
length delivery just outside off stump, Tendulkar goes back and across to punch it to covers
139.1 kmph short of length delivery that bounces outside off stump, Tendulkar goes back to punch it to backward point
goes back and across to punch it to covers
on the middle stump line, Tendulkar expected it to bounce a bit more than it did, crouches at the last minute to turn it to the on side
just outside off stump, from back of length, Tendulkar punches it off the back foot but can't pierce the off-side field again
short in length outside off, mistimes the cut to covers
full pitched outside off, hint of away swing but Tendulkar leaned across, covered the swing and caressed it through covers
on the middle, tilting in, full in length, flicked away to midwicket
on the off and middle stump line, worked to square-leg
on the middle stump line, on a length, worked wide of mid-on for a single
short in length and outside off, opens the bat-face to run it down to third man
fullish, on the middle, trying to get the lbw, Dravid was on the front foot, gets the foot out of the way and whips the ball through midwicket

ooh .. nasty little bouncer on this slow track, Dravid was on the hop, realised the ball was climbing higher than he thought it would, manages to drop his wrists and get the bat out of the way. Gem from Bondy
full pitched delivery this time, dug out to covers
full in length, outside off, around 139 kmph, Dravid edges the off drive to the on side .. good bowling this
aha! the slower one this time, ends up as a dipping full toss outside off, Dravid kills his initial thought to drive and pushes it out to the off side
short in length outside off, guided to backward point
bursts from short of length outside off, Dravid looks to defend and gets a bottom edge on it. He swings around, worried whether the ball would run back to the stumps but the ball rolls outside off
Mills errs by bowling it towards the middle and leg line and Tendulkar wrists it through midwicket to pick up a boundary
stays back to punch the back-of-length delivery to mid-on
around 132 kmph, fullish, on the middle, Tendulkar is late in getting forward, eventually does so to pick up a single with a push to the left of mid-on
fires in a bouncer, Dravid mistimes the pull down to long-leg. He didn't connect well.
full pitched around off and middle, Tendulkar works it to midwicket region
short in length, slower one, moves in, gets past the prod and clips the pad
from wide of the crease, 143.2 kmph length delivery tilting in towards middle and off, Dravid gets behind the line to nudge it to the on side
143.1 bouncing delivery from short of length, lovely delivery, Dravid does well to get on top of the bounce and punches it away to backward point.
139.1 kmph fuller delivery, well outside off , Dravid tries to reach out and gets a inner nick but falls well short of the keeper
short and wide, slapped hard but can't beat cover point.
a sharp bouncer on the middle, Dravid shapes to pull but ducks at the end. Wonder how the likes of Raina and co would have handled this hostile spell from Bond.
gets forward and behind the line of a fast length delivery to defend it to the off side
gets forward to push it past the bowler
length delivery on the middle stump, Tendulkar gets forward, shows the full face of the bat - his newly sponsored one, the MRF days are over, Adidas time now - to push the ball back down the pitch
moves forward to push the ball towards mid-off
134.5 kmph short delivery around off stump, comes on slowly, Tendulkar pulls it through wide midwicket
ah! It was the slower bouncer, around 114 kmph, on the middle, Tendulkar was cramped for room but managed to arch back and upper cut it down to third man
another slower one, around the off stump line, Tendulkar eases it to the off side
123.5 slower one, fullish,. Dravid tries to adjust to the lack of pace by wristing it but mistimes it towards mid-off

136.4 kmph short of length delivery bouncing in towards the off stump - he has bowled really really good on this slow track - Dravid gets behind the line to defend it to the on side. Dravid has played him very well too.
full pitched outside off, Dravid walks across to drive it hard, well timed shot, but can't beat the cover-point fielder
length delivery homing in on the off stump, around 140 kmph, Dravid gets solidly behind the line to defend
the bouncer arrives and Dravid allows it to pass over him.

ooh unlucky Bond. It was the slower one and he lured Dravid into the drive early but Dravid got an inside edge that took the ball past the stumps and to the fine-leg boundary. Lovely contest between the two.
starts well, gets some movement straightaway, nips back in sharply from short of a length outside off, fends it away into the leg side from the crease
and he/she watches Tendulkar smack that between point and cover for a boundary, short and wide, he rocked back and gave it the treatment
looking very confident is Tendulkar here, shortish outside off, rocks back and punches it sweetly to cover
forces it off the back foot to cover, just opened the face a touch, it's coming on nicely
whips it away stylishly off the back foot, bang on middle, slightly short, moves back, captures the length early and swipes it through square leg for four more. Awesomely skillful shot

Butler's been smacked around, lands on a good length outside off, drives it elegantly between cover and cover point, the early indications were that the ball would roll over the ropes comfortably but the outfield slows it down
slightly short and cut down to sweeper cover
flighted on the middle and off, opens the bat-face to steer it to cover point for a single
lovely turning delivery, Tendulkar was shaping to defend and the ball spun past his bat
